# DataviewJS — Busca Simples

## Buscar MERGE no Vault inteiro

```dataviewjs
const termo = "MERGE INTO".toUpperCase();

let pages = dv.pages();
let rows = [];

for (let p of pages) {
  let content = await dv.io.load(p.file.path);

  if (content && content.toUpperCase().includes(termo)) {
    rows.push([
      p.file.link,
      p.file.path
    ]);
  }
}

dv.table(["Arquivo", "Caminho"], rows);
```

---

## Ignorando old/

```dataviewjs
const termo = "MERGE INTO".toUpperCase();

let pages = dv.pages()
  .where(p => !p.file.path.toLowerCase().includes("old/"));

let rows = [];

for (let p of pages) {
  let content = await dv.io.load(p.file.path);

  if (content && content.toUpperCase().includes(termo)) {
    rows.push([
      p.file.link,
      p.file.path
    ]);
  }
}

dv.table(["Arquivo", "Caminho"], rows);
```

